          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
              <supportDesc material="perg">
                <extent>
                  <measure unit="content_pending" quantity="-1"/>
                </extent>
                <foliation/>
                <collation/>
                <condition>
                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>Vellum, about 6 ½ in. by 4 3/8, consisting of 65 leaves, many of which are
                        stained and some torn, especially foll. 9, 37, 57, 58, 64, and 65. The
                        quires, signed with letters, were originally nine in number, but the first
                        two are now lost, and ܓ and ܛ are imperfect. There are from 20 to 24 lines
                        in each page. </p>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </condition>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <p>Content pending</p>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="1">
              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" medium="unknown" scope="sole" script="syr">
                <desc>This manuscript is written in a small and rather inelegant hand of the xth or
                  xith cent.</desc>
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <additions>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <locus from="64b"/>
                  <p>The Psalms and the first three Canticles have been arranged for part-singing in
                    the choir, by means of the red letters ܐ and ܒ inserted between the lines. This
                    division, as well as that into ܫܘܒ̈ܚܐ. and ܡܪ̈ܡܝܬܐ seems to have been made, some
                    time after the manuscript was written, by a monk named Jacob; for, on the margin
                    of fol. 64 b, there is a note, now much effaced and torn, which begins: ܝܥܩܘܒ
                    ܚ̇ܛܝܐ ܦܪܫܗ ܟܬܦܐ ܩܕܡܝܐ ܐ ܘܐܚܪܝܐ ܒ ܟܕ ܟܠ ܡܪܡܝܬܐ "the sinner Jacob divided it (viz.
                    this psalter) into a first part (ܐ) and a second part (ܒ), each marmīthā…….”</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܝܥܩܘܒ ܚ̇ܛܝܐ ܦܪܫܗ ܟܬܦܐ ܩܕܡܝܐ ܐ ܘܐܚܪܝܐ ܒ ܟܕ ܟܠ ܡܪܡܝܬܐ</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
